# MultiFlexi Web Package

This package (`multiflexi-web`) contains the web interface components for MultiFlexi.

## Contents

This package includes:
- All PHP files from `src/*.php` 
- Web assets (CSS, JavaScript, images)
- MultiFlexi PHP classes from `src/MultiFlexi/`
- API endpoints from `src/api/`
- Web server configuration

## Dependencies

The package depends on:
- `multiflexi-common` - Base configuration and user setup
- `php-vitexsoftware-multiflexi-core` - Core MultiFlexi functionality
- `php-vitexsoftware-ease-html-widgets` - HTML widgets framework
- `php-vitexsoftware-ease-bootstrap4-widgets` - Bootstrap 4 widgets
- `libjs-jquery-datatables` - DataTables jQuery plugin
- `libjs-jquery-selectize.js` - Selectize.js for enhanced select boxes
- `php-cli` - PHP command line interface

## Installation

The web files are installed to `/usr/share/multiflexi/` and the package automatically configures Apache2 and Lighttpd web servers when they are present.

## Web Server Configuration

The package handles:
- Apache2 configuration via `/etc/apache2/conf-available/multiflexi.conf`
- Lighttpd configuration via `/etc/lighttpd/conf-available/50-multiflexi.conf`
- Proper file permissions for web files (www-data:www-data)

## Relationship to Other Packages

- `multiflexi` - Main package now recommends `multiflexi-web` instead of directly including web components
- `multiflexi-common` - Provides shared configuration used by web interface
- `multiflexi-api` - Provides REST API that the web interface can use
- `multiflexi-cli` - Command-line tools that complement the web interface

This separation allows for more flexible deployment scenarios where the web interface may not be needed on all installations.
